Class TermTabularDataFileReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.tabular.TermTabularDataFileReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, TabularDataFileReader<TermTabularDataLine>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DwcTabularDataFileReader

    public class TermTabularDataFileReader
extends Object
implements TabularDataFileReader<TermTabularDataLine>
    Warning: this class will probably be removed shortly Decorator of TabularDataFileReader to map elements of a line to a TermTabularDataLine. Supports the reading of lines smaller or larger than the declared set of columns.

      • getLastRecordLineNumber

        public long getLastRecordLineNumber()
        Description copied from interface: TabularDataFileReader
        The line number of where the last record returned by TabularDataFileReader.read() starts. If no records have been returned yet this method is expected to return 0. Once TabularDataFileReader.read() returned null, this methods will return the number of the last line in the file. Note that if the very last line is an empty line with only an endline character it will not be counted. Line number includes header line and empty lines (if applicable).
        Specified by:
        getLastRecordLineNumber in interface TabularDataFileReader<TermTabularDataLine>
        Returns:
        line number of where the last record starts
